            "subject": "LU-3978 nrs: ORR/TRR is using CRR-N fields"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Nikitas Angelinas",
          "email": "nikitas_angelinas@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2013-09-11 22:43:23.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-09-23 16:42:25.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-3430 nrs: Fix a race condition in the ORR policy",
        "message": "LU-3430 nrs: Fix a race condition in the ORR policy\n\nChecking the atomic oo_ref in nrs_orr_hop_put_free() and then\ntaking the bucket lock leaves a race window open, by which a\nsecond thread can attempt to free an already-freed\nnrs_orr_object. Fix this, and change the hash bucket lock type\nfrom an rwlock to a spinlock, as there are now as many calls on\nthe write path, as there are on the read path. Rehashing is not\nused on the hashes, so libcfs_hash API usage can also be\nsimplified.\n\nSigned-off-by: Nikitas Angelinas <nikitas_angelinas@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I2e16320c5e4b0803e1bef428f26ea18b0341ac5f\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-1294\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/7623\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Emoly Liu <emoly.liu@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Li Xi <pkuelelixi@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
